`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- `carveSplineIntoHeightmap` uses an O(V×S) scan (256 verts × ~64 samples = ~16k ops/path) — fast enough for chunk generation but could be optimized with a spatial hash if needed later.
- The "boundary exit point" design (path always terminates on a chunk edge) means adjacent chunks each generate a half-path that meets at the boundary — no cross-chunk coordination needed, pure per-chunk computation.
- With `LANDMARK_PROBABILITY = 0.15` and 4 neighbors, the expected number of paths from any landmark is ~0.6 (4 × 0.15). Adjusting this constant directly controls trail density worldwide.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
